      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: setup engine reliability fixes and unit tests",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nHanselman adversarial review (Opus + Codex dual-model) identified 18 issues in the setup engine. This PR fixes 12 reliability bugs and adds 66 unit tests.\n\n### HIGH consensus fixes (both models agreed)\n- **RetryExecutor**: wrap action() in try/catch - exceptions no longer crash the pipeline\n- **CommandRunner**: catch Win32Exception on process.Start() (e.g. missing wsl.exe)\n- **ConfigureGatewayStep**: shell-escape ExtraConfig values to prevent injection\n\n### Verified LOW consensus fixes\n- TryResetReloadModeAsync: use CancellationToken.None in finally block\n- TransactionJournal: catch IOException on writes (non-fatal degradation)\n- CleanupStaleGatewayStep: delete setup-state.json from both AppData and LocalAppData\n- AutoApprove: fall back to BootstrapToken when SharedGatewayToken is null\n- TrayArtifactCleanup: protect DeleteFileIfExists with try/catch\n- StartKeepaliveStep: remove unused stdout/stderr redirect that could stall\n- PairOperatorStep: unsubscribe DeviceTokenReceived handler in finally\n- Program: run TrayArtifactCleanup on Cancelled outcome (best-effort)\n- CleanupStaleDistroStep: retry VHD directory deletion with backoff\n\n### New test coverage (66 tests)\n- RetryExecutorTests (11), SetupPipelineTests (14), TransactionJournalTests (9)\n- SetupLoggerTests (7), SetupConfigTests (18), SetupContextTests (7)\n\n### Validation\n- build.ps1, Shared (1891), Tray (773), SetupEngine (66) tests all pass\n- E2E tests: 5 consecutive runs, all passed (avg 153s)",
